{"classification":{"category":{"name":"Wasm","normalized_name":"wasm","subcategories":[{"name":"Embedded Functions","normalized_name":"embedded-functions"}]}},"foundation":"CNCF","items":[{"category":"Provisioning","id":"provisioning--security-compliance--kubewarden","name":"Kubewarden","logo":"logos/24207e926905a8f8a35dce3be43c4da4f8d9e8edea46b2beb3c319d6857b8e7a.svg","subcategory":"Security & Compliance","website":"https://www.kubewarden.io","additional_categories":[{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"}],"description":"Kubewarden is a Policy Engine powered by WebAssembly policies. Its policies can be written in CEL, Rego (OPA & Gatekeeper flavours), Rust, Go, YAML, and others. Kubewarden simplifies Policy-As-Code by allowing policy authors and consumers to use their preferred tooling and stack, develop and test policies out of cluster. ","maturity":"sandbox","primary_repository_url":"https://github.com/kubewarden/kubewarden-controller","tag":["security"]},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","id":"orchestration-management--scheduling-orchestration--knative","name":"Knative","logo":"logos/6a1b7572490f95cada1836b3e0f932e5ff10c683bc1167b08ff868fb7867cfd5.svg","subcategory":"Scheduling & Orchestration","website":"https://knative.dev","additional_categories":[{"category":"Serverless","subcategory":"Installable Platform"},{"category":"Wasm","subcategory":"Embedded Functions"},{"category":"AI Native Infra","subcategory":"Orchestration and Scheduling"}],"description":"Knative is a developer-focused serverless application layer which is a great complement to the existing Kubernetes application constructs. Knative consists of three components: an HTTP-triggered autoscaling container runtime called “Knative Serving”, a CloudEvents-over-HTTP asynchronous routing layer called “Knative Eventing”, and a developer-focused function framework which leverages the Serving and Eventing components, called \"Knative Functions\".","maturity":"graduated","primary_repo